  "text": "Academic research has examined many biases including favorites, underdogs, the \"hot hand\" phenomena, and the popularity of teams. The NBA has been a popular setting for research on on betting biases. The present research focuses on the degree in which the popularity of NBA teams is priced into the point spread of NBA games, adding to the growing literature from [CITATION_1] research on additional fundamental factors that affect the point spread for NBA games.",
